{\rtf1\ansi \deff0{\fonttbl{\f8\fswiss Arial;}}\margl720\margr1920\pgnstart132\sectd\pgnrestart\pgnstarts132\footery1080{\header \pard\plain\ql MYARC ADVANCED BASIC\par }{\footer \pard\plain\ql \chpgn     VERSION 4.0  DDI SOFTWARE  \par }\pard \plain\f8\fs20 MYART--Subprogram\tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab MYART\par \par \par \par \par Format\par MYART(path.filename)\par \par Description\par CALL MYART(path.filename) loads and displays a MYART picture.\par \par Graphics mode must match before it is called.\par \par Example program to detect graphics mode\par \par 100 CALL RESETPLT\par 110 CALL GRAPHICS(4)\par 120 CLS\par 130 DISPLAY AT(20,10):"MYART path.filename"\par 140 ACCEPT AT(21,16)BEEP:MY$\par 150 OPEN #1:MY$,INPUT,DISPLAY,FIXED 128\par 160 INPUT #1:A$\par 170 CLOSE #1\par 180 IF SEG$(A$,2,1)=CHR$(0) THEN 200\par 190 CALL GRAPHICS(3,3) :: GOTO 210\par 200 CALL GRAPHICS(2,3)\par 210 CALL MYART(MY$)\par 220 CALL KEY(0,K,S) :: IF S<1 THEN 220\par 230 CALL RESETPLT\par 240 CALL GRAPHICS(4)\par \par \par \par NEW\tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab NEW\par \par \par \par Format \par NEW\par \par Description\par The NEW command erases the program currently in memory, so that you can enter a new program.\par \par The NEW command restores the computer to the condition it was in when you selected MYARC Advanced BASIC from the main selection list with the following exceptions:\par \par \tab The INIT subprogram does not effect the memory available for MYARC Advanced BASIC programs.\par \par \tab Assembly-language subprograms loaded by the LOAD subprogram remain in memory, but is a \par \tab separate memory and does not reduce the memory available for MYARC Advanced BASIC \par \tab programs.\par \par NEW restores all other default values, closes any open files, and cancels any BREAK  command in effect.\par }
